com.example.bettertrialbook.models

Class Trial

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.example.bettertrialbook.models.Trial
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.os.Parcelable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BinomialTrial, CountTrial, MeasurementTrial, NonNegTrial

    public abstract class Trial
extends java.lang.Object
implements android.os.Parcelable
    The abstract Trial class is a parent class for the four kinds of trials. This holds the id of the trial and the experimenter, information common to all types of trials such as a geolocation, a timestamp, and whether it is blacklisted. It also contains an abstract method getTrialType() to be implemented by each child class. Trial implements Parcelable so that it can be passed through intents between activities.
